## 12. Argue by contradiction
### Example
```coq
Lemma example_contradicition :
  ‚àÄ x ‚àà ‚Ñù,
    (‚àÄ Œµ > 0, x > 1 - Œµ) ‚áí
      x ‚â• 1.
Proof.
Take x ‚àà (‚Ñù).
Assume that (‚àÄ Œµ > 0, x > 1 - Œµ) (i).
We need to show that (x ‚â• 1).
We argue by contradiction.
Assume that (¬¨ (x ‚â• 1)).
It holds that ((1 - x) > 0).
By (i) it holds that (x > 1 - (1 - x)).
Contradiction.
Qed.
```
